    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn currently stable neovim 0.10 you can set lsp float borders by leveraging `vim.lsp.with`\n\n```lua\nlocal ms = lsp.protocol.Methods\nlocal float_opts = { border = 'single' }\n\nlsp.handlers[ms.textDocument_hover] = lsp.with(lsp.handlers.hover, float_opts)\nlsp.handlers[ms.textDocument_signatureHelp] = lsp.with(lsp.handlers.signature_help, float_opts)\n```\n\nThis no longer works in current master or future neovim 0.11 where you'd need to either override the builtin lsp keymaps such as `K` or `<C-s>` \n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'K', '<cmd>lua vim.lsp.buf.hover({border = \"single\"})<cr>')\nvim.keymap.set('i', '<C-s>', '<cmd>lua vim.lsp.buf.signature_help({border = \"single\"})<cr>')\n```\n\nor override the functions themselves\n```lua\nlocal _hover = vim.lsp.buf.hover\n\nvim.lsp.buf.hover = function(opts)\n    opts = opts or {}\n    opts.border = opts.border or 'single'\n    return _hover(opts)\nend\n```\n\nBoth ways seem overly verbose or complex for what is attempted to be achieved\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIdeally there would be a way to set default LSP float options similar to `vim.diagnostic.config`. Perhaps there is an argument on being able to set a default float options globally, but I want to keep this issue scoped to LSP floats specifically.\n\nI found this [comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/25514#issuecomment-1749023982) from Justin\n\n> `vim.foo.config` (`vim.diagnostic.config`) is a convention for cases that don't make sense as \"editor options\" (at least until we gain dict options and perhaps eventually namespace options).\n\nI know that `vim.lsp.config` is already taken, but perhaps there is a different name that can be used for this use case.\n\nUPD: use correct neovim versions. Current stable is 0.10 not 0.11, next is 0.11 not 0.12",
